  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "Beta Bequin — pariah, untouchable, and trained at the King's Wood school to be the perfect blank — discovers that the woman she was raised to become is a counterfeit of an older Alizebeth Bequin she was never meant to meet. The Eisenhorn and Ravenor arcs collide on the city-world of Sancour through a cold-war exchange between Inquisitor Gregor Eisenhorn (long radical, long believed-dead) and Inquisitor Gideon Ravenor (still rogue), each playing the other through Beta as the unwitting piece. The book opens the Bequin trilogy with the question: which side of the Inquisition is the real one, and which is using Beta — both? Cherubael is in it; Pontius Glaw is in it; everything that was buried in Hereticus is now walking.",
